Connect raspberry pi to laptop via ethernet cable and on laptop via control panel enable wifi sharing of ethernet so that pi can use wifi via laptop.

0) Setup OS on raspberry first then continue with steps below.

1) Create folder: 

mkdir expo-project

2) Open folder:

cd expo-project

3) Create virtual inveroment:

python3 -m venv opencv-env

4) Open virtual inveroment:

source opencv-env/bin/activate

5) Install opencv into virtual invorment:

pip install opencv-python

6) Leave virtual invorment:

deactivate

7) Install git globally:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install git -y

8) Verify install:

git --version

9) Then configure your identity:

git config --global user.name "same name github account"
git config --global user.email "same email github account"

10) Install pyqt5 designer (for GUI):

sudo apt install qttools5-dev-tools -y
sudo apt install qt5-default -y

11) Open virtual enviroment:

source opencv-env/bin/activate

12) Install pyqt5 in virtual enviroment:

pip install pyqt5
pip install pyqt5-tools
